      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "WAIKARIE VENOM (1) hit the ground running from an outside draw with a fast early split, holding on for a minor placing when third and beaten 5.5 lengths at Rockhampton over 407m in 23.80. Boasts five wins from nine starts out of this box. Can measure up this time. HOPE'S JACKY (2) turned in a solid run last start over 390m at this track finishing 5th and beaten only 4.5 lengths (22.20). Cannot be taken lightly. TUKI BEACH (4) is a capable type and proved too classy last time to win by 1.75 lengths at this track in a handy 19.72 beating Weather Man Rick. Recorded one of the quickest times on the card in scoring last start. Leading chance again. TUSKEN WARRIOR (5) raced handy last time and scored. That form reads well.",
